                            <comment id="13439848" author="jmhsieh" created="Wed, 22 Aug 2012 21:13:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this proposing to add types to hbase? (either by convention or internally?)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13440673" author="ionignat" created="Thu, 23 Aug 2012 21:15:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think it not about adding data types, it&apos;s more about adding SerDes support. Behind a common model(interface), it should be support for any standard data type: long, double, strings with different encoding, etc.&lt;br/&gt;
Also, in this way we could add support for any custom model(Ex: a table with a composed key, where firsts 4 bytes are an integer value, next eight are a long representing a date and the rest are a result of a hash function). In this way is much more easier to perform operations using shell. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13455781" author="mdrzal" created="Fri, 14 Sep 2012 13:37:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ionignat&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ionignat&quot;&gt;Ionut Ignatescu&lt;/a&gt; would &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6592&quot; title=&quot;[shell] Add means of custom formatting output by column&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6592&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6592&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; address your issues?  If so, it might make sense to just make this a dupe of that jira.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
